Engine.cpp uses the following code to do the time step smoothing:
 lastTimeSteps_.Push(elapsed / 1000000.0f);
    if (lastTimeSteps_.Size() > timeStepSmoothing_)
    {
        // If the smoothing configuration was changed, ensure correct amount of samples
        lastTimeSteps_.Erase(0, lastTimeSteps_.Size() - timeStepSmoothing_);
...
if timeStepSmoothing_ is bigger than 2, say 20, then everytime it will cause lastTimeSteps_.Erase() to execute , which in turn need to memmove 20 floats.  In stead of moving these floats ,we can use the PODVector as a circular buffer,  and use a formula to calculate the current time step:
timeStep_ = (timeStep_ \* timeStepSmoothing_ - lastTimeSteps_[currentIdx] + elapsed / 1000000.0L)
lastTimeSteps_[(++currentIdx)%timeStepSmoothing_] = elapsed/100000.0L;
Do you think this change is desirable?

